node.text:
Repost from @WaltDisneyImagineering: In preparation for the 50th Anniversary celebration of @WaltDisneyWorld, Imagineers from the Collections Management team recently oversaw the refurbishment of the Partners statue in Magic Kingdom Park. Originally created by famed Disney sculptor Blaine Gibson, this sculpture of Walt Disney holding the hand of Mickey Mouse has become an iconic photo location at our Disney theme parks around the world. To restore the statue to its original look, conservators stripped the sculpture to its bare metal before cleaning, reapplying patina and coating the entire figure in protective polymer and wax.

The Collections Management team helps to develop, design, curate and maintain more than a dozen galleries, and the vast collection of artwork and bronze statues that spans the breadth of the Walt Disney World Resort, including all four theme parks and many resort hotels.

With this work complete, and Cinderella Castle shimmering behind them with her royal makeover, Walt and Mickey are ready for The World’s Most Magical Celebration to begin on Oct. 1! #DisneyWorld50 ✨

node.text: The official app for the @Disneyland Resort is brimming with time-saving conveniences and enchanting ways to enhance your experience! View attraction wait times, mobile order food and drinks from select locations, and, coming soon, go right to your hotel room using online check-in and the new digital key. Learn more about the new features on the Disney Parks Blog (link in bio).

node.text: Keep your eyes peeled the next time you board the world-famous Jungle Cruise at @Disneyland park! A handful of “Easter eggs” are hidden throughout the attraction, and we’re tipping you off with just a few of them inspired by the #JungleCruise film on the Disney Parks Blog (link in bio). Watch for more “Easter eggs” at Magic Kingdom Park, and prepare for your next treasure hunt by catching Disney’s “Jungle Cruise” in theaters or order it on @DisneyPlus with Premier Access on July 30.
